name: Freedom.
description:
The West Irian Liberation Monument is a monument built to commemorate the Trikora fighters and the people of West Irian who chose to become part of the Republic of Indonesia. This monument is in the middle of Lapangan Banteng and is 35 meters high. The shape of the monument is a statue made of bronze.

I took this photo from the side to get a different feeling, especially the emotion of the statue itself. And using plants as my foreground to depict the statue that has been freed from the shackles.
